1 olive oil
2 potato
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
2 radish
1 packet salmon
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
1 packet tahini
2 tsp honey
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle over
chermoula spice blend, drizzle with olive oil,
season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then roast until tender,
20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice radish.
• Pat salmon dry with paper towel and season
both sides. Set aside.

• In a small bowl, combine chargrilled capsicum
relish, tahini and the honey. Set aside.

• When the potatoes have 10 minutes remaining,
heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook salmon, skin-side down
first, until just cooked through, 2-4 minutes
each side.

• While the salmon is cooking, combine radish,
shredded cabbage mix and a drizzle of vinegar
and olive oil in a large bowl. Season with salt
and pepper.

• Divide seared salmon, chermoula potatoes and
radish slaw between plates.
• Top salmon with capsicum tahini sauce to serve.
Enjoy!